'''David Santee''' was an [[United States|American]] [[Figure skating|figure skater]]. He is the [[1981 World Figure Skating Championships|1981 World silver medalist]] and an eight-time [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships|U.S. National]] medalist. He also competed at the [[Winter Olympics]] twice. His younger brother [[Jimmy Santee]] was also an elite-level skater.
Santee is an ISU Technical Specialist.<ref>{{PDFlink|[http://www.isu.org/vsite/vfile/page/fileurl/0,11040,4844-179484-196702-110011-0-file,00.pdf ISU Communication No. 1409]|381&nbsp;[[Kibibyte|KiB]]<!-- application/pdf, 390900 bytes -->}}</ref> He also works as a coach. Among his students is [[Agnes Zawadzki]], who he coached for seven years as a child and again since June 2011.<ref name=cc060311>{{cite news | url = http://usfigureskating.org/Story.asp?id=46208&type=media | title = 2010 U.S. Junior Champion Agnes Zawadzki Announces Coaching Change | last = | first = | date = June 3, 2011 | work = [[U.S. Figure Skating]] | accessdate = June 3, 2011}}</ref><ref name=dh061311>{{cite news | url = http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20110613/news/706139908/ | title = Des Plaines figure skater turns to old pro to help her move up | last = Daday | first = Eileen O. |date = June 13, 2011 | work = [[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]] | accessdate = June 13, 2011 }}</ref>
